<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-18T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-18T15:00:00-05:00" n="270" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/20761:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-18T16:00:00-04:00">April
                                        18, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>111. For Murphy. I am informed that should the present <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> even approximately be maintained
                                consideration will be given in due course to the recommendation
                                contained in your 203 of April 2, 10 a.m.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>